               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$d - Volumes/dates to which call number applies</strong> <div class="description">Statement used only when the call number does not apply to all items of the
                              series. <em>Applies to:</em> may be generated for display.
         </div>
         <div class="description2">
            <div class="description">May also contain a copy (or set) number.</div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Order</strong> - The 070 field for a <em>current</em> call number precedes the 070 field for an
                        <em>earlier</em> call number.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Capitalization</strong> - Alphabetic characters in the classification portion of the field are usually
                  uppercase.
      </div>
